from typing import List

class Solution:
    def partitionLabels(self, s: str) -> List[int]:
        # Create a dictionary to store the last occurrence of each character
        last_occurrence = {char: idx for idx, char in enumerate(s)}

        # Initialize variables to keep track of the current partition
        start, end = 0, 0
        partitions = []

        # Iterate over the string
        for idx, char in enumerate(s):
            # Update the end of the current partition to the last occurrence of the current character
            end = max(end, last_occurrence[char])

            # If we are at the end of the current partition, add its length to the partitions list
            if idx == end:
                partitions.append(end - start + 1)
                start = idx + 1

        return partitions
```

This solution works by first determining the last occurrence of each character in the string. It then iterates through the string, updating the end of the current partition to the last occurrence of the current character. When the current index matches the end of the partition, it means we can safely close the partition and start a new one. The size of each partition is calculated and added to the result list.
